headline: TE Connectivity reports significant progress toward long-term sustainability goals
summary: TE Connectivity, a world leader in connectors and sensors, has reduced Scope 1 and 2 greenhouse gas emissions by 80% between September 2020 and October 2024, outperforming its goal of a 70% reduction. This milestone is one example of the company's significant progress toward its long-term sustainability ambitions, detailed today in its annual One Connected World corporate responsibility report.
